1 unit(s) Tofu
1 unit(s) Sweet Potato
1 unit(s) Corn on the Cob
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
56 g Spring Mix
1 unit(s) Green Onion
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 tbsp Red Wine Vinegar
1 tbsp Jerk Spice Blend
2 tsp Sriracha
¼ tsp Sugar*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Peel, then cut sweet potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add sweet potatoes and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to a parchment-lined baking sheet. Season with salt, pepper and half the Jerk Spice Blend, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven, tossing halfway through, until golden-brown, 25-28 min.

Meanwhile, husk corn.
Halve cucumber lengthwise, then cut into 1/4-inch half-moons.
Thinly slice green onion.
Pat tofu dry with paper towels. Cut tofu in half parallel to the cutting board. (NOTE: You will have two square tofu steaks per block.) Using a fork, poke tofu all over.
Add tofu, half the sriracha, half the mayo and remaining Jerk Spice Blend to a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.

Add tofu to one side of the grill. Grill tofu, flipping once, until grill marked, 4-5 min per side.
While tofu cooks, add corn to the other side of the grill. Close lid and grill, turning occasionally, until tender and grill marks form, 8-10 min.
Transfer corn and tofu to a large plate.

Add vinegar, remaining sriracha, remaining mayo and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine.

When corn is cool enough to handle, with corn on its side, cut kernels from cob, turning cob as you go.
Add corn, cucumbers and spring mix to the bowl with salad dressing, then toss to coat.

Thinly slice tofu.
Divide salad and tofu between plates.
Top salad with roasted sweet potatoes.
Sprinkle with green onions.